investigation.title: Transcriptional analysis of colon from mice flown on the RR-6 mission
investigation.description: The objective of the Rodent Research-6 (RR-6) study was to evaluate muscle atrophy in mice during spaceflight and to test the efficacy of a novel therapeutic to mitigate muscle wasting. The experiment involved an implantable subcutaneous nanochannel delivery system (nDS; between scapula), which delivered the drug formoterol (FMT; a selective Beta-2 adrenoceptor agonist), over the course of time.

project.title: Rodent Research-6
project.funding: The sequencing analysis was funded by NASA Space Biology Program Office, Space Life and Physical Sciences Research and Applications Division.

publications.title: Counteracting Muscle Atrophy on Earth and in Space via Nanofluidics Delivery of Formoterol
